06/03/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government decided on Wednesday (March 5th) to hold the first round of local elections on June 1st, followed by a second on June 15th, if necessary. 
Initially, Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu had floated the idea of late May or early June, with the date of May 25th rumoured for the first ballot and June 8th for the second. 
Explaining the move to June 1st, Tariceanu noted the UEFA European Cup championship begins June 7th.
Also on Wednesday, President Traian Basescu and representatives of the biggest political parties, including the Social Democratic Party and the Greater Romania Party, signed a national plan to boost education. 
It would allocate 6% of Romania's GDP to the sector between now and 2013. 
(Nine o'clock - 06/03/08; Mediafax, Rompres - 05/03/08)
